  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0db0\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dab \u0d9a\u0ddc\u0db8\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0db8 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca \u0daf\u0dc3 \u0daf\u0dd9\u0db1\u0d9a\u0dd4\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dab\u0dd4 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dc3\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The Judicial Commission inquires from ten judges",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It is reported that the Judicial Service Commission has asked around ten Magistrates and District Judges to state why the investigations were conducted.",
        "It is also reported that when the country is in a state of crisis due to fuel and economic difficulties, the Judicial Service Commission has been informed by a circular not to take up cases other than essential cases.",
        "According to judicial sources, the Magistrates and District Judges have been informed to submit their observations within a week regarding the conduct of court proceedings despite being informed by a circular of the Judicial Service Commission.",
        "About a week after the Judicial Service Commission informed that the court proceedings should be held without delay due to the delay in the proceedings due to the covid epidemic situation, another circular was issued and informed that only the necessary proceedings should be conducted due to the crisis situation in the country."
      ],
